## Web Research Complete

**Queries**: 5 searches + 2 fetches executed
**Sources**: 10 relevant sources found
**Artifact**: `/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/d9d040bd645b03c4a9dec8316f715a5c/web-research.md`

### Key Findings

- **Dark theme CSS is mostly done** — `index.css` already has the design tokens (`--color-canvas: #0b1326`), `@custom-variant dark`, and `.dark body` rules. The critical missing piece is that `main.tsx` never adds the `dark` class to `<html>`. One `classList.add('dark')` call fixes activation.

- **Component colors bypass design tokens** — `App.tsx` root div uses `bg-white dark:bg-gray-900` instead of `bg-canvas`. Many components likely still use generic grays. A `grep` audit of `bg-white|bg-gray-` in `src/components/` will map the full scope.

- **Knowledge graph library already installed** — `react-force-graph-2d@^1.29.1` is in `package.json` and `GraphView.tsx` exists. No new dependencies needed; just needs seed data with `parent_ids` to show links.

- **Screenshot tests need richer seed data** — Current 3 mock Things are all generic tasks/notes. Should cover all 6 `type_hint` values (project, task, person, note, idea, event) with varied priorities, `checkin_date`s, and parent-child relationships. Chat history needs user+assistant turns and action-confirmation messages.

- **Dark screenshot test gap** — The existing dark test uses `page.emulateMedia({ colorScheme: 'dark' })`, which only works if the app responds to the media query to add the `dark` class. Should also test via `page.evaluate(() => document.documentElement.classList.add('dark'))`.

### Gaps

- Unclear how many components have been migrated to design tokens vs. still using generic Tailwind grays — needs a `grep` audit.
- Mobile "The Radar" view is not yet implemented (expected to be a follow-up issue per the issue description).

Sources:
- [Tailwind CSS Dark Mode](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/dark-mode)
- [Playwright Visual Comparisons](https://playwright.dev/docs/test-snapshots)
- [React Flow](https://reactflow.dev/)
- [Material Design 3 Chips](https://m3.material.io/components/chips/guidelines)
- [Playwright Visual Regression Guide 2026](https://bug0.com/knowledge-base/playwright-visual-regression-testing)
